Consider using `crypto.timingSafeEqual` to prevent timing attacks when comparing secrets. Also, handle the case where `REVALIDATE_SECRET` is not set.

Please add `import { timingSafeEqual } from "crypto";` to the top of the file.

```suggestion
  if (!REVALIDATE_SECRET) {
    console.error("REVALIDATE_SECRET environment variable not set.");
    return NextResponse.json({ message: "Internal Server Error" }, { status: 500, headers });
  }

  const providedSecretBuffer = Buffer.from(secret ?? "");
  const serverSecretBuffer = Buffer.from(REVALIDATE_SECRET);

  if (
    providedSecretBuffer.length !== serverSecretBuffer.length ||
    !timingSafeEqual(providedSecretBuffer, serverSecretBuffer)
  ) {
    return NextResponse.json({ message: "Invalid secret" }, { status: 401, headers });
  }
```

